ember.js web app showing one to many data models in action using ember-data

To run this django application

1. pip install -r requirements.txt
2. python manage.py syncdb
3. python manage.py runserver
4. http://localhost:8000/admin/
5. add a few sessions and speakers
6. open the source for the CreateModelMixin class and add this
    foo = self.get_instance_data(model, content, *args, **kwargs)
    del foo['session_id']
    instance = model(**foo)
**instead of this
    instance = model(**self.get_instance_data(model, content, *args, **kwargs))

To run the javascript unit tests you will need to install phantomJS

Ubuntu `apt-get install phantomjs`
OSX `brew install phantomjs`

Next run npm install to pull down the jasmine-phantom-node module

npm install

Now you can run the tests from the root like so

node node_modules/jasmine-phantom-node/bin/jasmine-phantom-node ember/static/script/tests
